outcomedescr: There was a significant delay in finding the scene as it was not at the entrance origionally stated or at any of the onsite buildings as was thought. After multiple call backs by dispatch, contact was made and a more accurate location was determined. Multiple vehicles were found at the location along with the individual whom EMS had been called for. The individual had been visiting the grave of her deceased husband (deceased X1 year). Her family stated that she had been shaky and not feeling well. When asked, she had said she could not get up, so EMS was called. On EMS arrival at the individual's location, she stated that she did not need assistance and when asked if she would be willing to have her vitals taken and a basic assessment she refused twice. A plan was confirmed with her family for someone to drive her home and be with her for the remainder of the evening.

ALL TIMES ARE APPROXIMANT.
PT HAD NO IDENTIFICATION OF ANY SORT. DELAYED ON SCENE FOR SEVERAL MIN. PT WOULD NOT LEAVE TO GO TO THE HOSPITAL TILL HE TALKED TO AN HALTON REGIONAL POLICE OFFICER AND TOLD HIM WHAT HAPPEN.

PT AT HOSPITAL WANTED TO USE THE PHONE, NURSE ALLOWED THIS, I NOTED THAT THE PT WAS WALKING NORMAL (HE WAS NOT STUMBLING ANYMORE)
